The paper discusses the risks associated with hacking internet-connected vehicles, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper analyzes the impact of such attacks on the transportation system, which can be categorized under cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also uses simulation and modeling techniques to analyze the impact of attacks, which can be categorized under simulation and modeling (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the need for secure software development practices, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the need for coordination and collaboration between different stakeholders to mitigate the risks, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY).
